President Obama and Michelle Obama send their well wishes to Coptic Orthodox Christians in the United States and worldwide for a joyful Christmas celebration. They express gratitude for the significant contributions Coptic Christians have made to the United States. The President also reaffirms the commitment of the United States to protect the rights of Christian and other religious minorities globally. He emphasizes the importance of freedom of religion and the ability to worship as one chooses for the development of a peaceful and inclusive society. In this Christmas season, the Obamas join Coptic Christians in praying for peace.